author: David Wolcott dwolcott@wickedlocal.com
title: SILVER LAKE XC: Lakers fall to Plymouth North
text: Posted Oct. 14, 2015 at 2:40 PM Updated at 2:40 PM dwolcott@wickedlocal.com Posted Oct. 14, 2015 at 2:40 PM KINGSTON - The Silver Lake cross country teams had no luck against Patriot League rival Plymouth North last Tuesday, falling by the score of 15-49 in the girls race while the boys dropped a 26-33 decision to the Blue Eagles. Andrea Noland was the first Lady Laker across the finish line, taking seventh in the time of 21 minutes, 36 seconds. Alli Tonsberg was the only other Silver Lake runner in the top 10, taking ninth place (22:23). Finding a spot in the top 20 were Kim Eldridge (13th), Ali Gavigan (14th), Bri Sheehan (15th), Lily Flaherty (16th), Julia Riordan (17th) and Michelle Van Arde was 20th. Also running for Silver Lake were Julia McGrath (23rd), Madelyn Casper (27th), Morgan McKenney (28th), Erin Sullivan (29th), Maggie McSherry (31st), Cierra Isakson (33rd) and Emily White was 34th. The Laker boys had three of the top five finishers, but Plymouth North's depth was the turning point of the meet. Colin Boerger was first across the line in a time of 16:49. Will Felix and Paul Cook tied for fourth with matching times of 17:28. Also finishing in the top 20 were Josh Bean (15th), Wes Kupic (16th) and Zac Michaud placed 19th. Silver Lake was back in action Tuesday against Duxbury. Email the reporter at dwolcott@wickedlocal.com and follow him on Twitter, @DavidWolcott1.
